<doc id="562079" wikidata="Q1377896" url="?curid=562079" title="European Latsis Prize">
<text>The European Latsis Prize is awarded annually by the European Science Foundation for &quot;outstanding and innovative contributions in a selected field of European research&quot;. The prize is worth 100,000 Swiss francs and is awarded within a different discipline each year. The prize was inaugurated in 1999 by the Latsis Foundation and ended in 2012. The prize was awarded in a different scientific field. 

